[1] Berry disease and leave rust, coffee - Uganda: spread
Date: Mon 5 Apr 2010
Source: The New Vision (Uganda) [edited]
<http://www.newvision.co.ug/D/8/13/715281>


Arabica coffee disease on the rise
----------------------------------
Coffee berry disease and leaf rust, which often affect arabica coffee, are
on the increase, the National Crops Resources Research Institute has said.
Africano Kangire disclosed that the diseases are affecting yields and need
urgent attention. In Uganda, arabica constitutes 20 per cent and robusta 80
per cent of the coffee crop.

"The coffee industry is faced with challenges including the intensification
of research in pests and diseases management and global warming resulting
in drought in some areas," Kangire said. He observed that resources are
inadequate and the Government is not seriously investing in coffee research.

[additional news story:
<http://news.tradingcharts.com/futures/3/8/137781083.html>]

[byline: John Kasozi]

